---
title: Pork Shoulder Steak with Braised Fennel, Onion & Apple and Roasted Potatoes
description: Just like a rib-eye steak, pork shoulders have lots of intramuscular fat (giving them a really rich flavour) and like strip steak, it has a lovely satisfying chew. Chef Andre recommends slicing the pork steaks thickly and pan frying it for a few minutes on each side to get the best flavour and texture. Paired with sweet caramelised apples, fennel and red onion, roasted potatoes and fresh parsley, this simple dish is set to become your new dinnertime favourite
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/pork-shoulder-steak-dcae4af4-b7983ef8.jpg
